<Layout
  title="About Me"
  description="About Behrad Saraiyeh — A Passionate Software Engineer"
  pubDate={new Date("March 19 2026")}
  heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
  <p>
    Hey, I’m <strong>Behrad Saraiyeh</strong> — I work in tech, mostly
    <strong>SRE, DevOps and Backend development</strong>.
  </p>

  <p>
    I started my journey when I was <strong>10</strong>, playing around with
    robotics — first mechanics and electronics, and then learning
    <strong>C</strong> and simple algorithm-focused languages to make my robots work.
    I got really good at it and ended up competing in international competitions —
    winning a <strong>Gold Medal</strong> at RoboCup Asia-Pacific 2018 in Thailand
    and becoming a member of
    <strong>Iran’s National Elites Foundation</strong>. At a pretty young age I
    also started <strong>teaching robotics to kids (7–18 years old)</strong> and later
    mentored teams in competitions.
  </p>

  <p>
    In 2023, I started studying
    <strong>Applied Mathematics</strong> at KNTU because I love math. While studying,
    I got into software development and taught myself
    <strong>React</strong> and <strong>Django</strong>. I also completed a
    backend internship that gave me real hands-on experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    While working on backend systems, I discovered how much I enjoyed
    <strong>DevOps</strong> — improving how systems actually run. I joined
    <strong>Gareno Pargas</strong>, where I owned the infrastructure end‑to‑end,
    from developer tooling to production systems, and focused on making things
    faster, more reliable, and easier to operate.
  </p>

  <p>
    Since that’s what I enjoyed most, I switched my major to
    <strong>Computer Engineering</strong> at IAU to better align with my work. After
    a solid run at Gareno Pargas, I joined <strong>SnappPay</strong> — the <strong
      >Fintech</strong
    >
    arm of <strong>Snapp Group</strong> — where I now work as an
    <strong>SRE</strong>, helping keep systems reliable and scalable for
    <strong>millions of users</strong>.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>
      I’m always trying to improve, get better at what I do, and chase bigger
      goals — both for myself and the systems I build.
    </strong>
  </p>
</Layout>
